channel.title: Acess is denied?
channel.description:
I compile my 562 client, and get this error,
[code=java]src\Applet_Sub1.java:20: error while writing Applet_Sub1: bin\Applet_Sub1.class (Access is denied) public abstract class Applet_Sub1 extends Applet ^ Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 1 error Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
Can anyone tell me what to do?

item.title: Acess is denied?
item.dc:creator: @madgamer madgamer
item.description:
@madgamer wrote:

Most of the time this would mean that you have a corrupted class file in your client folder. Try to delete all the files that end with .class and then compile again.
